Problem on Time, Speed and Distance-7 - Placement Exercise
NOTE: This kind of question is very common in campus placement ( TCS, Wipro, etc.) 
because it makes the use of simple formula and calculations.

Problem:
Rohit drives from his home at a speed of 30 km/hr and reaches his bank 20 minutes late.
Then the next day he increases his speed by 15 km/hr but still he is late by 8 minutes.
How far is his bank from his home?

Solution:
Note:  Add times when one is late and one is early â†’ because one increases time, the other decreases it
       Subtract times when both are late (or both early) â†’ because we want the difference due to speed change
       Time = Distance Ã· Speed

Let the distance between home and bank = D km

Time difference between the two speeds = 20 âˆ’ 8 = 12 minutes = 12/60 hours = 1/5 hours âœ…

Time at 30 km/h âˆ’ Time at 45 km/h = 1/5 hours
(D Ã· 30) âˆ’ (D Ã· 45) = 1/5
Take LCM of 30 and 45 = 90
(3D âˆ’ 2D) Ã· 90 = 1/5
D Ã· 90 = 1/5
D = 18 km âœ…

ğŸ‘ Final Answer:
Distance between Rohitâ€™s home and bank = 18 km
